                                AsterIDE.dev
                     Homepage for the AsterIDE Project

   asteride.dev

      This repository serves as the official homepage and entry point for
      all things related to AsterIDE — a simple, fast, and modern text
      editor written in Rust.

      The site acts as the main website for the AsterIDE ecosystem,
      providing documentation, updates, and general project information.

   Tech Stack.

      This website is built using Next.js (https://nextjs.org), with
      TypeScript and React for application structure and UI components,
      and Tailwind CSS for styling and layout.

   Contributing.

      Contributions are welcome.

      You may submit improvements or fixes via pull requests. All changes
      should be clear, focused, and consistent with the existing codebase
      style and structure.

   Security.

      If you discover a vulnerability or security issue affecting this
      website or any related AsterIDE service, you should not disclose it
      publicly.

      Instead, you may:

      (a) Open a non-public or private security report if available; or
      (b) Submit a pull request that directly addresses the issue.

      Reports should include, where possible:

      (a) A description of the issue;
      (b) Steps to reproduce;
      (c) Affected pages or components;
      (d) Any relevant technical details or proof of concept;

      All security reports will be reviewed and addressed as promptly as
      possible.

